The Demographics Unit
is in touch with half

26:42.100 --> 26:44.921
the country's
intelligence-gathering agencies.

26:44.970 --> 26:47.791
Now, if Da Silva was to give
even the flimsiest

26:47.840 --> 26:50.229
counterterrorism context
for wanting Pardillo Jr. found,

26:50.270 --> 26:52.704
then no good spook is going
to blink at that request.

26:52.740 --> 26:55.129
Well, why would he do
something like that?
Historically,

26:55.180 --> 26:57.671
money is the most effective
corruptor of lawmen.

26:57.710 --> 27:00.747
But there's always
the possibility that
the Ferrara family

27:00.780 --> 27:02.270
made him an offer
he couldn't refuse.

27:02.320 --> 27:04.788
Either way, Da Silva gave
the command, and a man

27:04.820 --> 27:07.311
who had eluded the Mafia
for more than two decades

27:07.350 --> 27:09.386
was found in a
few keystrokes.

27:09.420 --> 27:11.285
So what now?

27:11.330 --> 27:13.321
If we're gonna make
an allegation against

27:13.360 --> 27:15.294
the fourth-highest-ranking
police official in New York,

27:15.330 --> 27:17.764
we're gonna need more than
the shadovw utterances

27:17.800 --> 27:19.825
of some third-rate
Deep Throat.

27:19.870 --> 27:23.931
Investigating Da Silva
without alerting him is
going to be a challenge.

27:23.970 --> 27:26.768
We're going to
need some help.

27:27.840 --> 27:29.808
BELL: You guys are
really something.

27:29.840 --> 27:33.207
I can only imagine
what it must sound like.

27:33.250 --> 27:34.877
I'm sorry.

27:34.920 --> 27:36.217
(scoffs):
For which part?

27:36.250 --> 27:38.684
Lying and telling me
you needed me to come here

27:38.720 --> 27:40.915
to answer questions about
the morning I found the corpse,

27:42.360 --> 27:43.918
very well plot against him
at your office.

27:43.960 --> 27:46.224
Given the commissioner's
electronic omnisaence,

27:46.260 --> 27:49.821
I thought it wise
to provide a credible
pretext for our meeting.

27:49.860 --> 27:51.828
Just in case.
He's not corrupt.

27:51.870 --> 27:53.929
You don't have a shred of proof

27:53.970 --> 27:56.097
against him.
These accusations
are not my own.

27:56.140 --> 27:57.903
They come
from the NSA.

27:57.940 --> 27:59.430
But you are correct--

27:59.470 --> 28:01.404
we have no proof.

28:01.440 --> 28:03.101
That's why
you're here.

28:03.140 --> 28:05.199
Well...

28:05.250 --> 28:07.275
forget it.

28:07.310 --> 28:09.972
He assigned you
to investigate
an anonymous tip,

28:10.020 --> 28:13.319
which led directly
to the discovery of
Handsome Bobby's remains.

28:13.350 --> 28:15.352
Now, I cannot

28:15.390 --> 28:18.882
currently explain why
he may have wanted them found...

28:18.930 --> 28:20.898
but it's a startling coincidence

28:20.930 --> 28:23.967
that his was the name
the NSA decided to drop.

28:24.000 --> 28:26.867
Maybe you're just not as smart
as you think you are.

28:26.900 --> 28:28.993
Maybe the biggest
spy agency

28:29.040 --> 28:31.338
on the planet managed
to sell you a line.

28:31.370 --> 28:32.962
It's possible.

28:33.010 --> 28:35.331
But we want_ to make sure.
Bear in mind,

28:35.380 --> 28:37.132
if your boss
did decide to out Bobby,

28:37.180 --> 28:39.171
it's possible he did so
for a very good reason.

28:39.210 --> 28:40.848
The man may have
been a pederast,

28:40.880 --> 28:42.472
or a homegrown terrorist,
or both.

28:42.520 --> 28:44.044
I can conceive
of any number

28:44.090 --> 28:45.341
of _scenarios where
this all gets swept

28:45.390 --> 28:47.517
under the rug, but we
should know the truth

28:47.550 --> 28:50.348
before we decide,
don't you agree?

28:50.390 --> 28:53.791
You know, I expect
this kind of garbage from him.

28:57.500 --> 28:59.889
Excuse me.

29:03.240 --> 29:05.003
Detective?
Uh, you said your piece.

29:05.040 --> 29:07.201
I'm not gonna sit here
and listen to you
smear a good cop.

29:07.240 --> 29:09.003
It's not about smearing,
this is about...

29:09.040 --> 29:11.042
What is it with you?! Huh?

29:11.080 --> 29:13.071
What, I-I won't
forgive you,
so you want

29:13.110 --> 29:16.045
to send me on a witch hunt,
wreck my career?

29:16.080 --> 29:18.082
Oh, your "career"? Is that
what you're calling it, is it?

29:18.120 --> 29:19.883
Sitting behind a desk,
analyzing data?

29:19.920 --> 29:22.115
Oh, I'm sorry, wasn't it
you who, just two days ago,

29:22.160 --> 29:24.025
told my boss you wanted
a piece of the action?

29:24.060 --> 29:26.028
I was attempting to get
a rise out of you,

29:26.060 --> 29:28.153
to remind you that
no matter where you go

29:28.200 --> 29:30.054
or how tedious
the work you undertake,

29:30.100 --> 29:32.193
it will not change what
you are-- a detective.

29:32.230 --> 29:33.959
I am a detective.

29:34.000 --> 29:35.558
Well, you still carry
the title, yeah.

29:35.600 --> 29:37.329
But it's more than that,
isn't it?

29:37.370 --> 29:39.964
It's a calling.
It's your calling.

29:40.010 --> 29:43.036
You are not an analyst;
you are not an assessor of data.

29:43.080 --> 29:45.105
You transferred from Major
Crimes either because your pride

29:45.150 --> 29:47.914
would not allow you to occupy
the same space as me

29:47.950 --> 29:49.872
or because you're feeling
sorry for yourself.

29:49.920 --> 29:51.444
In either case,
a pathetic excuse.

29:51.490 --> 29:53.446
I have a tremor in my hand.

29:53.490 --> 29:56.254
I can't shoot,
can't get out on the street

29:56.290 --> 29:58.588
and work cases because of you!

29:58.630 --> 30:01.394
Bollocks! You could've _
stayed in Major Crimes until
you completed your rehab!

30:01.430 --> 30:03.967
You're assuming my rehab
can be completed!

30:04.000 --> 30:05.262
Because I have
faith in you!

30:05.300 --> 30:06.961
I have faith in
your perseverance!

30:08.270 --> 30:10.238
Be my friend,
don't be my friend--

30:10.270 --> 30:12.101
whatever--
but don't be so foolish

30:12.140 --> 30:15.507
as to confuse punishing me
with punishing yourself!

30:17.310 --> 30:20.939
You know what I thought
the first time I met you?

30:22.350 --> 30:24.910
Man, it comes easy
for that guy.

30:24.950 --> 30:26.247
Oh.

30:26.290 --> 30:28.383
Well, I'm sorry.

30:28.420 --> 30:31.583
It doesn't come that easy
to the rest of us.

30:31.630 --> 30:35.191
I am a drug addict, Marcus.

30:35.230 --> 30:36.492
A drug addict.

30:36.530 --> 30:38.919
And it might seem
like an abstraction to you

30:38.970 --> 30:41.165
_ because I have been sober
Since I made your acquaintance.

30:41.200 --> 30:43.634
But two years ago,
I was as pitiable a soul

30:43.670 --> 30:45.137
as you will ever meet.

30:47.010 --> 30:49.308
With help, I fought back,

30:49.340 --> 30:52.343
and I got a little bit better.

30:52.380 --> 30:56.248
I know what I'm supposed
to do with my life.

30:56.280 --> 30:59.078
Do you?

31:09.400 --> 31:12.221
(sighs)
This doesn't feel right.

31:13.700 --> 31:17.067
Well, forget your fantasies
of stone-walled Mafia compounds,

31:17.100 --> 31:19.568
it's actually quite a good place
to "go to the mattresses."

31:19.610 --> 31:21.202
It's incongruous.

31:21.240 --> 31:23.379
I'm not saying that we've
got the wrong place.

31:23.410 --> 31:25.549
I don't think Big Teddy's
mistress lied to us.

31:25.580 --> 31:28.515
Neither would you with
the threat of deportation
hanging over your head.

31:28.550 --> 31:30.415
Rather fiendish of you.

31:33.320 --> 31:36.983
of accusing a violent
crime boss of having
a cop on the take

31:37.020 --> 31:38.578
without backup.

31:38.630 --> 31:42.350
Well, I suppose we could
always announce our arrival.

31:42.400 --> 31:44.095
(blowing whistle loudly)

31:44.130 --> 31:46.428
All right, make it quick.

31:46.470 --> 31:49.598
Couple of...
police errand boys

31:49.640 --> 31:52.165
(chuckles):
or whatever you are.

31:52.210 --> 31:54.371
Well, actually, Mr. Ferrara,
we suspect you

31:54.410 --> 31:57.436
of having a police errand boy
of your own, and that's

31:57.480 --> 31:58.947
why we're here.

31:58.980 --> 32:00.447
That right?
You fancy yourself

32:00.480 --> 32:03.938
a businessman-- so which
of these deals sounds better?

32:03.990 --> 32:06.982
You tell us how Dante Scalice
managed to locate

32:07.020 --> 32:10.080
Handsome Bobby Pardillo,
and in exchange,

32:10.120 --> 32:11.348
we will not divulge

32:11.390 --> 32:13.187
your assistance.
Or...

32:13.230 --> 32:15.653
don't tell us what you know,
and you can add

32:15.700 --> 32:18.260
two new enemies _
to a long and growmg list.

32:18.300 --> 32:20.359
(chuckles)
You threatening me?

32:20.400 --> 32:22.231
We think it's only
a matter of time

32:22.270 --> 32:24.067
before police prove
that Scalice was working

32:24.110 --> 32:27.432
under your orders
when he killed Bobby Pardillo.

32:27.470 --> 32:28.607
Give us the name
of the officer

32:28.640 --> 32:30.471
we believe you have
on your payroll,

32:30.510 --> 32:32.546
and we will talk to our captain,
see if a deal can't be struck.

32:32.580 --> 32:34.275
We don't have a cop.

32:34.320 --> 32:36.345
Dante didn't have a cop.

32:36.380 --> 32:39.588
And if one of you has sent him
that packet, it's news to me,

32:39.620 --> 32:41.588
and it's your problem.

32:41.620 --> 32:43.485
Packet?

32:43.520 --> 32:46.057
FERRARA: Dante got it in
the mail ten days ago,
out of nowhere.

32:46.090 --> 32:48.058
"A bolt from the blue," he said.

32:48.100 --> 32:51.024
Telling me that there's all
this crap about our old friend.

32:51.070 --> 32:52.423
I said to him, "You know what?

32:52.470 --> 32:55.689
Who cares about
Bobby Pardillo anymore?"

32:55.740 --> 32:59.301
You think I like being out here
in the sticks

32:59.340 --> 33:01.001
with a gun under my pillow?

33:02.640 --> 33:05.768
See, I didn't tell him
to do what he did.

33:05.810 --> 33:10.213
And you can take that back
to your, uh, pigpen.

33:10.250 --> 33:14.050
Sir, uh, Casey said I might
be able to get a minute?

33:14.090 --> 33:15.455
Of course.

33:15.490 --> 33:17.651
I just wanted to talk
to you about something.

33:17.690 --> 33:19.749
When Holmes came over here
the other day,

33:19.790 --> 33:21.758
he asked you
about the tip we got

33:21.800 --> 33:24.496
about the barrels?
Yeah.

33:24.530 --> 33:26.327
It's just... he reached out
to me this morning.

33:26.370 --> 33:27.667
He thought the tip
might have been fake.

33:27.700 --> 33:29.531
(scoffs)
Fake?

33:29.570 --> 33:33.301
He thinks maybe someone
wanted us to find that body.

33:33.340 --> 33:35.501
To what end?

33:35.540 --> 33:37.531
Not a clue.

33:37.580 --> 33:40.469
But that's sort of what
I wanted to talk to you about.

33:40.510 --> 33:43.070
You know my history
with the guy, and now you see

33:43.120 --> 33:44.815
that some of the theories
he comes up With

33:44.850 --> 33:46.408
can be pretty out there,

33:46.450 --> 33:48.315
and I just don't think

33:48.360 --> 33:51.488
he'll be a good fit around here.

33:51.530 --> 33:53.657
Consider him gone.

33:53.690 --> 33:55.829
I trust your judgment.

33:55.860 --> 33:58.420
Just not about the Knicks.

33:58.470 --> 34:01.394
WATSON: We officially need
a new pizza place.

34:01.440 --> 34:03.089
This one is taking forever!

34:03.140 --> 34:05.608
We visit a Mobster in hiding,
and you order Italian.

34:05.640 --> 34:07.335
Can a Godfather marathon
be far behind?

34:07.370 --> 34:08.632
It certainly seemed

34:08.680 --> 34:10.568
like Big Teddy was
telling the truth, right?

34:10.610 --> 34:12.168
But if Da Silva wasn't working

34:12.210 --> 34:13.609
for the Ferraras,
I don't get it.

34:13.650 --> 34:15.572
There is no trace of any grudge

34:15.620 --> 34:16.814
against Handsome Bobby
in the old case files.

34:16.850 --> 34:19.114
Well, perhaps the motive
is not from the past,

34:19.150 --> 34:20.515
but from the present.

34:20.550 --> 34:21.585
We must ask ourselves,

34:21.620 --> 34:23.611
"What might compel

34:23.660 --> 34:26.288
"a decorated officer
to risk his career

34:26.330 --> 34:29.356
_ in order to facilitate the
demise of a washed-up gangster?"

34:29.400 --> 34:32.267
(knocking on door)
Oh. Finally.

34:32.300 --> 34:35.497
(sighs)
You know what?

34:35.540 --> 34:38.703
Maybe after dinner,
we can... Marcus.

34:40.170 --> 34:41.501
Come in.

34:41.540 --> 34:43.303
Thanks.

34:47.710 --> 34:50.315
So, I, uh...

34:50.350 --> 34:52.648
I had a talk
with the deputy commissioner.

34:52.690 --> 34:53.816
You shared our suspicions?

34:53.850 --> 34:56.387
I asked him about
the tipster,

34:56.420 --> 34:58.650
same as you,
and he didn't blink.

34:58.690 --> 35:00.851
He was comfortable, open.

35:00.890 --> 35:03.120
But there was something
in his voice.

35:03.160 --> 35:05.390
It bothered me.
Couldn't tell you why.

35:05.430 --> 35:07.421
You have instincts.

35:07.470 --> 35:09.290
My point is,
I wanted to know.

35:09.340 --> 35:10.659
I had to.

35:10.700 --> 35:12.258
So I walked him out,

35:12.310 --> 35:14.369
and I doubled back.

35:14.410 --> 35:16.537
Found this in
his office.

35:16.580 --> 35:17.899
What is it?

35:17.940 --> 35:20.602
Proof that you were right.
He's dirty.

35:26.950 --> 35:29.180
It's a career case.
It's three career cases.

35:29.220 --> 35:31.359
The deputy commissioner
has enough there

35:31.390 --> 35:32.926
to put Robert Pardillo
behind bars

35:32.960 --> 35:35.394
for about a thousand years.

35:35.430 --> 35:36.852
Well, if you line up
the sentences

35:36.900 --> 35:38.367
back to back,
you might be right.

35:38.400 --> 35:40.618
Accessory to
murder, racketeering,

35:40.670 --> 35:42.365
tampering with union elections.

35:42.400 --> 35:45.858
I still can't believe
how old some of this stuff is.

35:45.910 --> 35:48.276
Da Silva must have been working
on this since the '705.

35:48.310 --> 35:49.709
BELL: It makes no sense.
He had the goods

35:49.740 --> 35:52.470
on a Mob boss for over 30 years,
never told a soul.

35:52.510 --> 35:55.240
Then he flips the guy's son
to his enemies?

35:55.280 --> 35:56.508
This was in the file.

35:56.550 --> 35:58.211
Yeah, I noticed.

35:58.250 --> 36:01.549
The handwriting
is Robert Pardillo's.

36:01.590 --> 36:04.423
I just compared it to a sample
the police had on file.

36:04.460 --> 36:06.325
The article was written
12 days ago,

36:06.360 --> 36:08.328
a mere 48 hours
before Dante Scalice

36:08.360 --> 36:11.420
received the packet which helped
him locate Handsome Bobby.

36:11.470 --> 36:13.825
Everything else in the dossier
predates the Internet.

36:13.870 --> 36:16.634
This could be the straw that
broke the camel's back.

36:16.670 --> 36:19.309
But it's just an article
on a union election.

36:19.340 --> 36:20.967
It could also be
the Rosetta Stone

36:21.010 --> 36:23.274
which unlocks the meaning of the
file, and gives us Da Silva's

36:23.310 --> 36:25.471
true motive.
Which was?

36:25.510 --> 36:27.307
He sacrificed Pardillo
Junior in an effort

36:27.350 --> 36:29.318
to wriggle out from under
Pardillo Senior's thumb.

36:29.350 --> 36:30.772
That doesn't make any sense.

36:30.820 --> 36:32.742
Doesn't it?
Think it through.

36:32.790 --> 36:34.849
The oldest evidence here
dates back

36:34.890 --> 36:38.485
to Da Silva's first year
as a beat cop in Murray Hill.

36:38.530 --> 36:39.929
He's been cleaning up

36:39.960 --> 36:41.825
the Pardillo family's
messiest missteps

36:41.860 --> 36:43.919
since he joined the force,
which strongly suggests why

36:43.960 --> 36:46.360
he was put on the force
in the first place.

36:46.400 --> 36:48.368
Da Silva is Deputy Commissioner.

36:48.400 --> 36:49.594
You think he's a Mob plant?

36:49.640 --> 36:52.461
At first.
But as you say, he rose.

36:52.510 --> 36:54.705
You_can't achieve his rank
Via subterfuge alone.

36:54.740 --> 36:57.379
He was, by all accounts,
an excellent police officer.

36:57.410 --> 37:00.800
I believe_he was converted
to his new cause.

37:00.850 --> 37:02.715
The guy's closing in
on a gold watch.

37:02.750 --> 37:05.412
It's a little late in the day
to grow a conscience,

37:05.450 --> 37:07.884
don't you think?
Louis Martinez.

37:07.920 --> 37:08.955
His candidate
for treasurer

37:08.990 --> 37:10.719
of the local 127--

37:10.760 --> 37:13.854
a construction union which has
prowded health benefits

37:13.890 --> 37:16.723
and a steady income to the
Pardillo family for the last

37:16.760 --> 37:18.318
50 years.

37:18.370 --> 37:20.463
Martinez is a reformist,
churchgoing citizen.

37:20.500 --> 37:22.434
His election would be
a crippling blow

37:22.470 --> 37:24.028
to a decaying
crime family.

37:24.070 --> 37:25.799
That clipping...

37:25.840 --> 37:29.276
Is a death sentence--
yes, I suspect so.

37:29.310 --> 37:30.834
(knocking on door)
Oh.

37:33.510 --> 37:36.274
BELL:_You're not
suggesting Da Silva's

37:36.320 --> 37:38.311
been ordered to kill
this Martinez guy?

37:38.350 --> 37:40.409
His role will
most likely be

37:40.450 --> 37:43.317
to cover up the murder, as it
has been so often in the past.

37:43.360 --> 37:46.488
BELL: All right,
back up a second.

37:46.530 --> 37:47.929
Why have Handsome Bobby killed?

37:47.960 --> 37:49.496
Having him killed

37:49.530 --> 37:50.929
was not the point.

37:50.960 --> 37:52.393
Having him found dead was.

37:52.430 --> 37:53.727
And with due respect
to your contribution,

37:53.770 --> 37:55.465
Da Silva orchestrated

37:55.500 --> 37:56.967
both the death
and the discovery.

37:57.000 --> 37:58.763
I imagine that he tracked

37:58.810 --> 38:01.472
Scalice's progress
with an assist from Big Brother.

38:01.510 --> 38:04.479
He wanted a Mob war.
A chain reaction

38:04.510 --> 38:06.068
of violent reprisals

38:06.110 --> 38:08.340
which would at least
weaken the Pardillo family.

38:08.380 --> 38:10.439
At best, it would result
in the death

38:10.480 --> 38:12.448
of the one man_
who knew his origins.

38:12.490 --> 38:14.856
The only way Da Silva
sails off into retirement

38:14.890 --> 38:16.585
is if the boss dies.

38:16.620 --> 38:18.383
That file is unusable

38:18.430 --> 38:20.421
as a nuclear arsenal.

38:20.460 --> 38:22.325
He kept it solely
to remind Pardillo

38:22.360 --> 38:24.590
of their mutually-assured
destruction.

38:24.630 --> 38:26.666
Well, it won't be much use
to a DA, either.

38:26.700 --> 38:28.463
I stole it from his office.

38:28.500 --> 38:31.401
_ It would be inadmissible
in any case against Da Silva.

38:31.440 --> 38:33.499
He might not go to jail, but
he certainly won't keep his job.

38:33.540 --> 38:35.076
Neither would
the detective.

38:35.110 --> 38:36.532
Fortunately, I don't think

38:36.580 --> 38:39.401
that level of self-sacrifice
Will be necessary.

38:41.780 --> 38:43.577
All right, thanks.

38:43.620 --> 38:44.939
Uh, Commissioner?

38:44.990 --> 38:46.946
Thought you'd
want to hear this.

38:46.990 --> 38:50.517
The lab was able to link the car
bomb that killed Dante Scalice

38:50.560 --> 38:53.882
to explosives from one of Robert
Pardillo's construction offices.

38:53.930 --> 38:56.353
Apparently, they went and
pulled the security tapes.

38:56.400 --> 38:58.425
They got the old man
giving the nod himself.

38:58.470 --> 39:00.563
Is that right?
Captain Gregson said

39:00.600 --> 39:02.033
he's gonna hold off
on the warrant

39:02.070 --> 39:03.799
till they know
Pardillo's whereabouts,

39:03.840 --> 39:06.400
but with a little luck, should
be wrapped up by end of day.

39:06.440 --> 39:11.377
Well, that's a damn fine
collar for Tommy Gregson.

39:11.410 --> 39:13.002
You tell him I said so.

39:13.050 --> 39:15.678
All right.

39:18.020 --> 39:21.786
(phone ringing)

39:21.820 --> 39:23.981
DA SILVA:
Robert?
You're late.

39:24.020 --> 39:25.681
I'm on my way.

39:25.730 --> 39:27.425
What the hell is the matter
with you?

39:27.460 --> 39:29.155
I shouldn't even be showing
my face here.

39:29.200 --> 39:30.553
DA SILVA:
There's a nice Barolo

39:30.600 --> 39:32.124
down in the galley.
Go help yourself.

39:32.170 --> 39:34.832
Be there in 15.

39:34.870 --> 39:37.566
PARDILLO:
I don't think you understand
the spot that I'm in.

39:37.600 --> 39:39.409
Yeah, I know.

39:39.440 --> 39:41.738
You got problems.
You got problems.

39:41.780 --> 39:44.499
But we gotta get
on the same page,

39:44.550 --> 39:46.472
how we're handling Martinez.

39:46.510 --> 39:48.842
Bobby, I wouldn't
have asked you here

39:48.880 --> 39:51.542
if it wasn't serious, huh?

39:51.590 --> 39:52.739
Something you got to see.

39:52.790 --> 39:54.451
Won't take five minutes.

39:54.490 --> 39:56.151
BELL (over bullhorn):
Commissioner Da Silva,

39:56.190 --> 39:58.556
put down your weapon.
You're surrounded.

39:59.790 --> 40:01.599
(siren wailing)
Police! Don't move!

40:01.630 --> 40:03.450
Stay right there!
Do not move!

40:03.500 --> 40:04.694
Let me see your hands!

40:04.730 --> 40:06.425
(siren whoops)

40:06.470 --> 40:07.425
OFFICER:
Clear the boat!

40:07.470 --> 40:09.028
Robert Pardillo...

40:09.070 --> 40:11.061
come out with your hands
behind your head.

40:11.100 --> 40:13.000
(sirens wailing)
It's safe.

40:13.040 --> 40:15.429
We're not gonna let the
deputy commissioner hurt you.

40:15.480 --> 40:17.675
OFFICER:
All right, lock it down! Go!

40:17.710 --> 40:19.575
(siren whoops)
Move! Move!

40:21.550 --> 40:23.438
A silencer.

40:23.480 --> 40:25.584
You were gonna take me
on a boat ride?

40:25.620 --> 40:26.609
You son of a bitch!

40:26.650 --> 40:29.187
(grunting)
Come over here,

40:29.220 --> 40:31.051
you rat bastard!

40:31.090 --> 40:33.479
(sirens approaching)

40:35.530 --> 40:40.820
(sirens continue,
getting closer)

40:44.840 --> 40:47.729
"We're not gonna let him
hurt you" was a nice touch.

40:47.770 --> 40:50.637
(laughs quietly)

40:50.680 --> 40:53.501
(indistinct radio communication
in distance)

40:53.550 --> 40:54.812
No kidding.

40:54.850 --> 40:56.613
(laughs)

40:56.650 --> 40:58.845
I bet he did.

41:00.190 --> 41:01.953
And-and thank you, sir.

41:01.990 --> 41:04.254
All right. Bye.

41:04.290 --> 41:06.053
You're allowed a television

41:06.090 --> 41:08.490
in your room
at Beacon Correctional, correct?

41:08.530 --> 41:10.020
You could hear all that?

41:10.060 --> 41:11.493
I couldn't.

41:11.530 --> 41:12.861
The deposed deputy
commissioner is going

41:12.900 --> 41:14.731
to a minimum security
facility upstate

41:14.770 --> 41:16.567
for the remainder
of his natural-born life.

41:16.600 --> 41:18.602
He struck a deal.

41:18.640 --> 41:21.200
You testify against Robert
Pardillo and his entire family,

41:21.240 --> 41:23.504
you get basic cable.

41:23.540 --> 41:24.973
I would have thought
bread and water would suffice.

41:25.010 --> 41:26.500
Well, he's never gonna
have a good night's

41:26.550 --> 41:27.801
sleep again.
That's for sure.

41:27.850 --> 41:29.977
Department's gonna take
a black eye on this one.

41:30.020 --> 41:31.510
(groans)

41:31.550 --> 41:33.984
Small price to pay
for cutting out a cancer, no?

41:34.020 --> 41:35.681
GREGSON:
While you're here,

41:35.720 --> 41:37.187
I wanted to thank you

41:37.220 --> 41:39.529
for straightening everything
out with Marcus.

41:39.560 --> 41:41.949
It's good to
have him back.
What?

41:51.140 --> 41:52.835
They're good-looking kids, man.

41:52.870 --> 41:54.838
Yeah, they're
gonna love you.

41:54.880 --> 41:58.543
The crazy guy at Dad's office
who bankrolled their new bikes.

41:58.580 --> 42:00.002
For a desk.

42:00.050 --> 42:01.870
Well, you sold low.

42:01.920 --> 42:03.672
I would've went
twice as high.

42:03.720 --> 42:05.585
You're an odd one, Bell.

42:05.620 --> 42:07.986
Don't know what
to tell you, man.

42:08.020 --> 42:10.011
It's my desk.

42:12.130 --> 42:14.724
*

